EmailTemplate.subject: Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber} - {!Case.Subject}
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Contact.Name},
Thank you for your interest in joining BSP {!Case.Country__c}.
In order for us to be able to process your application kindly ensure that the following documentation is submitted to IATA:
IATA BSP Airline Participation Joining Form: Please complete the form in electronic typewritten format (i.e. not handwritten) with all the information requested, and then sign and certify it with your Companys official stamp.
Bank Account Mandate: For settlement purposes your Airline must provide IATA with a Banking Mandate for each BSP country:
1. The mandate can be provided in two forms: Local bank account in the BSP Country and Currency or IATA Currency Clearance Service (ICCS) contract for cross border payments instructions. For more information on ICCS please visit http://www.iata.org/service/finance/iccs/Pages/index.aspx
2. If you would like to use a local bank account, please note that the corresponding mandate must be issued as per the attached instructions and template, on the participants letterhead, and signed at your Airlines Head Office by two 2 senior officers at least one of which must be:
o the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) or
o Head of Treasury or Cash Management Department
For countries/operations with dual currencies, the bank mandate needs to be submitted per currency.
The bank mandate must be provided with the joining package and will be handled within the joining timeline of 35 days.
Please complete the form in electronic typewritten format (i.e. not handwritten) with all the information requested, and then sign and certify it with your Companys official stamp.
The process will begin once all original documents are received at the Geneva Head Office at the below address:
Global Airline Participation Team
International Air Transport Association
33, Route de l'Aroport
1215 Geneva 15 Airport
Switzerland
Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber}
Fees:
A Joining Fee of USD is required to process the request Please visit the following link for Airline Central Billing information, such as Price List 2014, Central & Regional Management Fees and SCUs: http://www.iata.org/services/finance/Pages/airline-central-billing.aspx
Payment Procedure: Once all original documents have been received and validated by IATA, an invoice will be issued to the airline. If the airline is an IATA Clearing House member, then the payment will be handled through this option. However, should the airline join via IBCS, the fees will be collected by IBCS.
Credit Card Sales:
Please note that the BSP only settles cash sales. If your Airline wishes to open credit card sales in a given market, you will need to setup a valid merchant agreement with the credit card acquirers of your choice. IATA has developed some products that allow you to handle credit card sales in a more efficient manner, providing detailed reports to facilitate Head Office reconciliation:
ECCB Electronic Credit Card Billing: This service provides your credit card acquirers with daily files with information on credit card transactions processed by the BSP, allowing them to credit your Airline for the required amounts. In addition, a daily file is uploaded on your Airline BSPlink or iiNet account.
(IATA CardClear and IATA CardAXS), that allow the airlines to accept payment cards worldwide in local currencies. These products simplify the payment process (reduced number of card acceptance merchant agreements and processing contracts), reduce network distribution costs (favorable terms and conditions) and provide consolidated and centralized settlement in multiple currencies at favorable rates. More information is available at http://www.iata.org/services/finance/Pages/airlines.aspx.
Please do not hesitate to contact this office,by replying to this email, in case of any further queries/assistance. Our team will be glad to assist you accordingly.
For future support in regards to any other query, please log a new inquiry through our customer portal at http://www.iata.org/customer-portal/Pages/contactus.aspx
We look forward to hearing from you shortly.
Thank you,
{!Case.OwnerFullName},
Global Airline Participation Team
Financial and Distribution Services
International Air Transport Association
33, Route de l'Aroport
1215 Geneva 15 Airport
Switzerland
www.iata.org/customer
